title: The HTML charset Attribute
text: The character set is specified in the <meta> tag:
The HTML5 specification encourages web developers to use the UTF-8 character set.
UTF-8 covers almost all of the characters and symbols in the world!

title: The ASCII Character Set
text:
ASCII was the first character encoding standard for the web.
It defined 128 different characters that could be used on the internet:

title: The ANSI Character Set
text: ANSI (Windows-1252) was the original Windows character set:

title: The ISO-8859-1 Character Set
text:
ISO-8859-1 was the default character set for HTML 4. This character set 
supported 256 different character codes. HTML 4 also supported UTF-8.

HTML 4 Example

<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=ISO-8859-1">

HTML 5 Example

<meta charset="ISO-8859-1">
